        <section style="margin-top: 2rem; border-top: 2px solid var(--asha-gold); padding-top: 2rem;">
            <h2 style="color: var(--mythos-primary);">Historical & Philosophical Significance</h2>
            <p>Asha represents one of humanity's earliest philosophical concepts of absolute truth and cosmic order. Its influence extends beyond Zoroastrianism:</p>
            <ul style="margin: 0.5rem 0 0 2rem; line-height: 1.8;">
                <li><strong>Ethical Monotheism:</strong> Influenced Jewish, Christian, and Islamic concepts of divine law</li>
                <li><strong>Cosmic Justice:</strong> Inspired concepts of karma, divine judgment, and moral causation</li>
                <li><strong>Truth as Divinity:</strong> Equation of truth with ultimate reality influenced philosophy and mysticism</li>
                <li><strong>Moral Dualism:</strong> Framework for understanding good vs. evil as cosmic principles</li>
                <li><strong>Human Responsibility:</strong> Emphasis on human choice and moral agency in cosmic drama</li>
        </section>
